				<w:rPr>
					<w:b />
				</w:rPr>
				<w:t>Export from 6.x Server</w:t>
			</w:r>
			<w:r>
				<w:t> allows you to export the objects and data from your SQL Server 6.x installation. If you are upgrading using the tape data transfer method, you may choose to upgrade in two steps: an export only to tape, followed by an import only to your SQL Server 7.0 installation after you have increased your free disk space. For a named pipe data transfer, this option is always selected. It is strongly recommended that you select this option, and, whenever possible, upgrade with a single pass through the wizard that uses the </w:t>
			</w:r>
